<item>
            <title>[JCR-2216] Append-only index updates</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2216</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Currently index updates modify some existing files. This is troublesome in scenarios like a backup or when an index will be shared in a cluster (though this is not yet the case).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Requirements are:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- index segments need a custom (lucene) IndexDeletionPolicy to keep index commits for a given time.&lt;br/&gt;
- index segments are not only referenced by their name, but also with their generation&lt;br/&gt;
- the segments file must now also record the generation of a segment. the file itself must be generational itself.&lt;br/&gt;
- purging of outdated index segment commits&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
